In article <19990103184105.A4538@tantalophile.demon.co.uk>,
Jamie Lokier <lkd@tantalophile.demon.co.uk> writes:
>> If you want that write a user mode daemon - it is a trivial modification
>> of tcpdump.   
> It is?  I've never found a tcpdump that works with PPP and current
> kernels.  Anyway, having seen how many errors I've missed because
> they're not logged (the faulty IP headers), I'll be looking at the SNMP
> data in future.
Grab the updated tcpdump/libpcap packages from ftp.inr.ac.ru:/ip-routing
They use the new (PF_PACKET, SOCK_DGRAM) facilities in 2.2 which hide
all the link layer specific details in the kernel and allow a generic
libpcap. 
